013package org.apache.juneau.bean.html5;

015import java.net.*;

017import org.apache.juneau.annotation.*;

020/**
021 * DTO for an HTML <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/forms.html#the-input-element">&lt;input&gt;</a>
022 * element.
023 *
024 * <p>
025 * The input element represents a form control that allows users to input data. It is a void element
026 * that can take many different forms depending on the type attribute, including text fields, checkboxes,
027 * radio buttons, file uploads, and more. The input element is one of the most versatile and commonly
028 * used form controls in HTML.
029 *
030 * <h5 class='section'>Examples:</h5>
031 * <p class='bcode w800'>
032 *    <jk>import static</jk> org.apache.juneau.bean.html5.HtmlBuilder.*;
033 * 
034 *    <jc>// Text input field</jc>
035 *    Input <jv>input1</jv> = <jsm>input</jsm>(<js>"text"</js>)
036 *       .name(<js>"username"</js>)
037 *       .placeholder(<js>"Enter your username"</js>)
038 *       .required(<jk>true</jk>);
039 * 
040 *    <jc>// Email input with validation</jc>
041 *    Input <jv>input2</jv> = <jsm>input</jsm>(<js>"email"</js>)
042 *       .name(<js>"email"</js>)
043 *       .placeholder(<js>"your@email.com"</js>)
044 *       .autocomplete(<js>"email"</js>);
045 * 
046 *    <jc>// File upload input</jc>
047 *    Input <jv>input3</jv> = <jsm>input</jsm>(<js>"file"</js>)
048 *       .name(<js>"avatar"</js>)
049 *       .accept(<js>"image/*"</js>)
050 *       .multiple(<jk>true</jk>);
051 * 
052 *    <jc>// Checkbox input</jc>
053 *    Input <jv>input4</jv> = <jsm>input</jsm>(<js>"checkbox"</js>)
054 *       .name(<js>"subscribe"</js>)
055 *       .value(<js>"yes"</js>)
056 *       .checked(<jk>true</jk>);
057 * 
058 *    <jc>// Password input with pattern</jc>
059 *    Input <jv>input5</jv> = <jsm>input</jsm>(<js>"password"</js>)
060 *       .name(<js>"password"</js>)
061 *       .pattern(<js>".{8,}"</js>)
062 *       .title(<js>"Password must be at least 8 characters"</js>);
063 * </p>
064 *
065 * <p>
066 * The following convenience methods are provided for constructing instances of this bean:
067 * <ul class='javatree'>
068 *    <li class='jc'>{@link HtmlBuilder}
069 *    <ul class='javatree'>
070 *       <li class='jm'>{@link HtmlBuilder#input() input()}
071 *       <li class='jm'>{@link HtmlBuilder#input(String) input(String)}
072 *    </ul>
073 * </ul>
074 * </p>
075 *
076 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
077 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/JuneauBeanHtml5">juneau-bean-html5</a>
078 * </ul>
079 */
080@Bean(typeName="input")
081@FluentSetters
082public class Input extends HtmlElementVoid {
083
084   /**
085    * Creates an empty {@link Input} element.
086    */
087   public Input() {}
088
089   /**
090    * Creates an {@link Input} element with the specified {@link Input#type(String)} attribute.
091    *
092    * @param type The {@link Input#type(String)} attribute.
093    */
094   public Input(String type) {
095      type(type);
096   }
097
098   /**
099    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/forms.html#attr-input-accept">accept</a> attribute.
100    *
101    * <p>
102    * Specifies which file types the file input should accept. Used with <c>type="file"</c>.
103    *
104    * <p>
105    * Examples:
106    * <ul>
107    *    <li><js>"image/*"</js> - Accept all image files</li>
108    *    <li><js>".pdf,.doc,.docx"</js> - Accept specific file extensions</li>
109    *    <li><js>"image/png,image/jpeg"</js> - Accept specific MIME types</li>
110    * </ul>
111    *
112    * @param accept File type restrictions for file uploads.
113    * @return This object.
114    */
115   public Input accept(String value) {
116      attr("accept", value);
117      return this;
118   }
119
120   /**
121    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/forms.html#attr-input-alt">alt</a> attribute.
122    *
123    * <p>
124    * Alternative text for image submit buttons. Used with <c>type="image"</c> to provide
125    * accessible text when the image cannot be displayed.
126    *
127    * @param alt Alternative text for image submit buttons.
128    * @return This object.
129    */

132      return this;

135   /**
136    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/forms.html#attr-fe-autocomplete">autocomplete</a> attribute.
137    *
138    * <p>
139    * Controls whether the browser can automatically complete the input field.
140    *
141    * <p>
142    * Common values:
143    * <ul>
144    *    <li><js>"on"</js> - Allow autocomplete (default)</li>
145    *    <li><js>"off"</js> - Disable autocomplete</li>
146    *    <li><js>"name"</js> - Full name</li>
147    *    <li><js>"email"</js> - Email address</li>
148    *    <li><js>"username"</js> - Username or login</li>
149    *    <li><js>"current-password"</js> - Current password</li>
150    *    <li><js>"new-password"</js> - New password</li>
151    *    <li><js>"tel"</js> - Telephone number</li>
152    *    <li><js>"url"</js> - URL</li>
153    *    <li><js>"address-line1"</js> - Street address</li>
154    *    <li><js>"country"</js> - Country name</li>
155    *    <li><js>"postal-code"</js> - Postal code</li>
156    * </ul>
157    *
158    * @param autocomplete Autocomplete hint for the input field.
159    * @return This object.
160    */
161   public Input autocomplete(String value) {
162      attr("autocomplete", value);
163      return this;
164   }

186    * <p>
187    * Whether the command or control is checked.
188    *
189    * <p>
190    * This attribute uses deminimized values:
191    * <ul>
192    *    <li><jk>false</jk> - Attribute is not added</li>
193    *    <li><jk>true</jk> - Attribute is added as <js>"checked"</js></li>
194    *    <li>Other values - Passed through as-is</li>
195    * </ul>
196    *
197    * @param checked
198    *    The new value for this attribute.
199    *    Typically a {@link Boolean} or {@link String}.
200    * @return This object.

204      return this;

209    *
210    * <p>
211    * Specifies the name of a hidden form field that will be submitted along with the input value,

217    *
218    * @param dirname The name of the hidden field for directionality information.
219    * @return This object.
220    */
221   public Input dirname(String value) {
222      attr("dirname", value);
223      return this;
224   }

620   /**
621    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/forms.html#attr-input-type">type</a> attribute.
622    *
623    * <p>
624    * Specifies the type of form control to display.
625    *
626    * <p>
627    * Common values:
628    * <ul>
629    *    <li><js>"text"</js> - Single-line text input (default)</li>
630    *    <li><js>"password"</js> - Password input (characters are masked)</li>
631    *    <li><js>"email"</js> - Email address input with validation</li>
632    *    <li><js>"number"</js> - Numeric input with spinner controls</li>
633    *    <li><js>"tel"</js> - Telephone number input</li>
634    *    <li><js>"url"</js> - URL input with validation</li>
635    *    <li><js>"search"</js> - Search input field</li>
636    *    <li><js>"date"</js> - Date picker</li>
637    *    <li><js>"time"</js> - Time picker</li>
638    *    <li><js>"datetime-local"</js> - Date and time picker</li>
639    *    <li><js>"checkbox"</js> - Checkbox input</li>
640    *    <li><js>"radio"</js> - Radio button input</li>
641    *    <li><js>"file"</js> - File upload input</li>
642    *    <li><js>"submit"</js> - Submit button</li>
643    *    <li><js>"button"</js> - Generic button</li>
644    *    <li><js>"reset"</js> - Reset form button</li>
645    *    <li><js>"hidden"</js> - Hidden input field</li>
646    * </ul>
